This paper discusses Bayesian networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for probabilistic reasoning. The paper also discusses inference mechanisms, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The topic of similarity networks and their extensions may fall under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the generalized representation scheme may involve information theory (cs.IT).
